{"add":{"doc":{"id":"b7490545b1f0d7477051afdfe75ad262425428bb63adf8cf4ab7756eb69decdd","url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/30/Hearst_Castle_Casa_Grande_September_2012_panorama_2.jpg/170px-Hearst_Castle_Casa_Grande_September_2012_panorama_2.jpg","previous":[],"after":["Beginning in 1919, Hearst began to build Hearst Castle, which he was destined never to complete, on a 240,000 acres (97,000 hectares) ranch at San Simeon, California, which he furnished with art, antiques and entire rooms brought from the great houses of Europe. He also used the ranch for an Arabian horse breeding operation. San Simeon was also used in the 1960 film Spartacus as the estate of Marcus Licinius Crassus (played by Laurence Olivier)."]}}}